We have $|\pi - 7| = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
\pi - 7 & \mbox{if } \pi > 7 \\
7 - \pi & \mbox{if } \pi < 7 \\
\end{array}
\right.$.  Therefore, $\left|\pi - |\pi - 7|\right| = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
\pi - (\pi - 7) & \mbox{if } \pi > 7 \\
\pi - (7 - \pi) & \mbox{if } \pi < 7 \\
\end{array}
\right.$.

Since $\pi$ is clearly greater than 7, $\left|\pi - |\pi - 7|\right| = \pi - (\pi - 7) = \boxed{7}$.

We have $|\pi - 7| = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
\pi - 7 & \text{if $\pi > 7$,} \\
7 - \pi & \text{if $\pi < 7$.}
\end{array}
\right.$Therefore,
\begin{align*}
\left| \pi - |\pi - 7| \right| &= \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
\pi - (\pi - 7) & \text{if $\pi > 7$,} \\
\pi - (7 - \pi) & \text{if $\pi < 7$.}
\end{array}
\right. \\
&= \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
